WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.971 --> 00:00:14.306
Yeah. I got it.

2
00:00:14.389 --> 00:00:17.643
This is my favorite part.
[stammers] I just fucking love this.

3
00:00:17.726 --> 00:00:18.727
I'm coming up.

4
00:00:19.394 --> 00:00:21.021
You know what strikes me
when I watch this?

5
00:00:21.688 --> 00:00:22.940
I mean. apart from the obvious.

6
00:00:23.023 --> 00:00:25.567
I mean… [scoffs] …what the fuck. right?

7
00:00:26.318 --> 00:00:28.987
No. what strikes me is how you're moving.

8
00:00:29.571 --> 00:00:32.323
You're not sneaking around.
You're not rushing through it.

9
00:00:32.406 --> 00:00:34.368
Cool as the other side of the pillow. man.

10
00:00:35.202 --> 00:00:37.371
- You're a pro.
- Well. if I was such a pro.

11
00:00:37.454 --> 00:00:39.039
you wouldn't have
that video there. would you?

12
00:00:39.122 --> 00:00:41.542
Yeah. well. don't beat yourself up.

13
00:00:42.334 --> 00:00:44.127
My security system isn't installed yet.

14
00:00:44.211 --> 00:00:47.005
but I always plant a few hardwired i-PROs
around the house.

15
00:00:47.548 --> 00:00:49.716
I deal with a lot of dangerous people.

16
00:00:49.800 --> 00:00:55.347
and I've cultivated a level of paranoia
that most people would find excessive.

17
00:00:56.014 --> 00:00:58.350
- Please sit.
- [sighs]

18
00:00:59.309 --> 00:01:00.477
I can explain.

19
00:01:00.561 --> 00:01:01.937
Can you really?

20
00:01:05.774 --> 00:01:08.068
Is this a Thomas Crown Affair
kind of thing?

21
00:01:08.735 --> 00:01:12.239
Rich guy. so bored with his life.
he risks it all just to feel alive?

22
00:01:13.073 --> 00:01:15.158
Well. let's be honest.
you're not that rich.

23
00:01:15.242 --> 00:01:17.744
I mean. this place… any of it legit?

24
00:01:17.828 --> 00:01:19.246
You managing some money?

25
00:01:19.329 --> 00:01:21.123
Just trying to dig myself out.

26
00:01:21.206 --> 00:01:23.166
Well. look. man. no judgment here.

27
00:01:23.250 --> 00:01:25.043
I like a guy who colors outside the lines.

28
00:01:25.127 --> 00:01:26.378
I appreciate that.

29
00:01:27.212 --> 00:01:28.463
But look… [stammers]

30
00:01:29.798 --> 00:01:31.758
I just got to tell ya.
I'm really sorry about this.

31
00:01:31.842 --> 00:01:33.093
It's nothing personal. you know.

32
00:01:33.177 --> 00:01:34.928
I just figured you'd never miss it.

33
00:01:35.012 --> 00:01:36.555
The thing is. that's where you're wrong.

34
00:01:37.681 --> 00:01:41.852
See. 'cause that book isn't just
a first edition Wharton in mint condition…

35
00:01:43.270 --> 00:01:44.938
it was a gift from my wife.

36
00:01:45.606 --> 00:01:48.609
And it means more to me
than I could ever explain.

37
00:01:50.903 --> 00:01:52.446
I assume you still have it?

38
00:01:53.947 --> 00:01:55.866
[sighs] Not exactly.

39
00:01:57.743 --> 00:01:59.536
I'm gonna need that book back. Coop.

40
00:02:04.958 --> 00:02:06.335
I'm late for a meeting.

41
00:02:07.961 --> 00:02:11.798
So. to be clear.
you're not gonna turn me in?

42
00:02:15.552 --> 00:02:17.930
How about you just worry
about getting that book back?

43
00:02:21.892 --> 00:02:23.018
[door closes]

44
00:02:30.484 --> 00:02:31.777
[sighs]

45
00:02:34.947 --> 00:02:35.948
[sighs]

46
00:02:36.031 --> 00:02:38.408
[theme song playing]

47
00:02:41.161 --> 00:02:46.542
♪ A paper shadow
In a house of stone ♪

48
00:02:46.625 --> 00:02:51.672
♪ The wooden flag
Of a drifting dreamboat ♪

49
00:02:51.755 --> 00:02:55.884
♪ I never knew
How far the ride was gonna go ♪

50
00:02:55.968 --> 00:02:59.429
♪ Till I looked back
At the smoke ♪

51
00:02:59.513 --> 00:03:04.685
♪ You can't keep up
With the Joneses ♪

52
00:03:04.768 --> 00:03:09.606
♪ Don't wanna run
For the roses ♪

53
00:03:09.690 --> 00:03:14.862
♪ I got my pocket of posies ♪

54
00:03:14.945 --> 00:03:17.447
♪ Sometimes I wonder why ♪

55
00:03:17.531 --> 00:03:19.992
♪ Sometimes I wonder why ♪

56
00:03:20.075 --> 00:03:25.205
♪ I just don't run
With the Joneses ♪

57
00:03:25.289 --> 00:03:30.335
♪ Don't wanna smell
The dying roses ♪

58
00:03:30.419 --> 00:03:35.424
♪ I got my pocket
Full of posies ♪

59
00:03:35.507 --> 00:03:40.470
♪ I don't keep up
With the Joneses ♪

60
00:03:54.568 --> 00:03:56.111
[clerk] Please rise.

61
00:03:57.529 --> 00:03:59.031
I hereby declare. on oath…

62
00:03:59.114 --> 00:04:01.200
[all] I hereby declare. on oath…

63
00:04:01.283 --> 00:04:03.702
…that I absolutely and entirely…

64
00:04:03.785 --> 00:04:07.247
[all] …that I absolutely and entirely
renounce and abjure

65
00:04:07.331 --> 00:04:11.627
all allegiance and fidelity
to any foreign prince. potentate.

66
00:04:11.710 --> 00:04:13.629
- state or sovereignty…
- [clerk] So help me God.

67
00:04:13.712 --> 00:04:15.130
[all] So help me God.

68
00:04:16.005 --> 00:04:17.423
Congratulations. citizens.

69
00:04:17.507 --> 00:04:21.553
[all cheering]

70
00:04:33.815 --> 00:04:36.193
[bell chimes. toilet flushes]

71
00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:45.202
- Good morning.
- I'm late.

72
00:04:46.495 --> 00:04:47.496
You look nice.

73
00:04:47.579 --> 00:04:50.624
Oh. yeah? I was worried
that this blazer screams.

74
00:04:50.707 --> 00:04:52.751
"My brother doesn't think
I can handle this job."

75
00:04:53.335 --> 00:04:54.878
So yes to still mad?

76
00:04:54.962 --> 00:04:56.797
I… Let's not do this right now. huh?

77
00:04:56.880 --> 00:04:58.465
I didn't say you couldn't handle the job.

78
00:04:58.549 --> 00:05:00.092
And I didn't say I was still mad.

79
00:05:00.175 --> 00:05:01.468
- Ali. wait.
- I gotta go.

80
00:05:03.011 --> 00:05:04.388
How are you getting there?

81
00:05:07.182 --> 00:05:10.018
If you take me.
I will consider forgiving you.

82
00:05:23.407 --> 00:05:24.741
[dog barking]

83
00:05:32.916 --> 00:05:36.211
You go ahead.
you fake fucking bitch. Mm-hmm.

84
00:05:42.509 --> 00:05:43.760
Mel Cooper?

85
00:05:43.844 --> 00:05:45.345
You recognized me.

86
00:05:45.429 --> 00:05:47.014
- [both chuckle]
- Of course.

87
00:05:47.097 --> 00:05:48.223
How are you. Jeff?

88
00:05:48.307 --> 00:05:50.475
- [stammers]
- God. you look exactly the same.

89
00:05:50.559 --> 00:05:51.560
[chuckles]

90
00:05:51.643 --> 00:05:54.062
Well. must be that portrait
tucked in my attic.

91
00:05:54.146 --> 00:05:56.273
[both laugh]

92
00:05:56.356 --> 00:05:58.609
- I wish I had one of those.
- [laughs]

93
00:05:58.692 --> 00:06:00.068
To what do I owe the pleasure?

94
00:06:00.819 --> 00:06:03.655
Um. you know.
you saw my daughter recently.

95
00:06:03.739 --> 00:06:04.865
- Tori.
- Yes.

96
00:06:04.948 --> 00:06:07.075
- Bright kid.
- Yeah. a little too bright sometimes.

97
00:06:07.159 --> 00:06:10.829
Uh… She did call
our interview "pro forma."

98
00:06:10.913 --> 00:06:11.955
God. I'm so sorry.

99
00:06:12.039 --> 00:06:15.876
You know. she has just
not really been herself.

100
00:06:15.959 --> 00:06:16.960
Hmm.

101
00:06:17.044 --> 00:06:18.795
To be honest. we've just. um…

102
00:06:20.172 --> 00:06:21.924
been going through some stuff at home.

103
00:06:24.760 --> 00:06:25.802
Are you okay?

104
00:06:29.389 --> 00:06:31.350
Do you mind if I come in for a minute?

105
00:06:32.226 --> 00:06:34.269
- Yeah. sure. Come on in.
- I'm not bothering you?

106
00:06:34.353 --> 00:06:35.896
No. not at all. Come on in.

107
00:06:35.979 --> 00:06:38.315
- [Mel] Thank you so much.
- Yeah. Yeah. yeah. yeah.

108
00:06:38.398 --> 00:06:40.359
[students chattering]

109
00:06:40.442 --> 00:06:42.110
[Coop] Okay. first day of school.

110
00:06:47.115 --> 00:06:48.283
My God.

111
00:06:48.867 --> 00:06:49.868
[inhales deeply]

112
00:06:50.827 --> 00:06:52.329
Private school kids make me nervous.

113
00:06:52.412 --> 00:06:54.164
Oh. come on. They're gonna love you.

114
00:06:54.248 --> 00:06:56.333
[sighs] Well. of course
they're gonna love me.

115
00:06:56.416 --> 00:06:57.668
Everyone loves me.

116
00:06:57.751 --> 00:06:59.378
I'm worried I'm gonna hate them.

117
00:07:00.087 --> 00:07:01.797
- That's the spirit.
- [scoffs]

118
00:07:03.215 --> 00:07:04.299
Thanks for the ride.

119
00:07:04.383 --> 00:07:05.384
Yeah.

120
00:07:06.385 --> 00:07:08.470
- Be nice.
- Mm-hmm.

121
00:07:11.515 --> 00:07:12.516
Coffee.

122
00:07:13.642 --> 00:07:15.269
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

123
00:07:17.938 --> 00:07:18.939
[sighs]

124
00:07:25.863 --> 00:07:28.657
- But… I don't know.
- [indistinct chattering]

125
00:07:30.033 --> 00:07:31.243
Dad's here.

126
00:07:33.996 --> 00:07:35.956
[sighs] Disappointment tour. round two.

127
00:07:37.708 --> 00:07:38.709
Good luck.

128
00:07:47.259 --> 00:07:48.260
Good morning.

129
00:07:48.886 --> 00:07:50.679
- You look tired.
- [Coop] Thanks.

130
00:07:51.305 --> 00:07:52.306
Hey. hey. hey.

131
00:07:54.183 --> 00:07:55.350
My mind's made up. Dad.

132
00:07:56.101 --> 00:07:58.103
I'm not trying to change it.

133
00:07:58.187 --> 00:07:59.188
Really?

134
00:08:01.440 --> 00:08:02.983
I just wish you'd walk me through it.

135
00:08:04.193 --> 00:08:05.485
Get some sleep. Dad.

136
00:08:09.698 --> 00:08:11.825
[heartbeat thumping]

137
00:08:15.996 --> 00:08:17.456
[clicks tongue] Okay.

138
00:08:19.875 --> 00:08:21.543
Everything looks good.

139
00:08:23.378 --> 00:08:25.172
- It… It does?
- Mm-hmm.

140
00:08:25.923 --> 00:08:27.799
I take it this pregnancy wasn't planned?

141
00:08:27.883 --> 00:08:29.593
- Definitely not. no.
- Yeah. no.

142
00:08:31.094 --> 00:08:33.263
Wait. why?
Does the baby look poorly planned?

143
00:08:33.347 --> 00:08:34.847
The baby's fine.

144
00:08:34.932 --> 00:08:36.933
It's just that you're
at the end of your first trimester.

145
00:08:37.017 --> 00:08:38.727
Normally. you would have come in sooner.

146
00:08:38.809 --> 00:08:40.938
Yeah. I guess we just figured
we were safe.

147
00:08:41.020 --> 00:08:44.191
you know. with my geriatric uterus.

148
00:08:44.274 --> 00:08:46.693
Uh. the updated term is
"advanced maternal age."

149
00:08:46.777 --> 00:08:49.154
- That's not much better.
- Grace. let me assure you.

150
00:08:49.238 --> 00:08:51.615
you have the uterus of a 25-year-old.

151
00:08:51.698 --> 00:08:53.033
- Just like your ass.
- Okay.

152
00:08:53.116 --> 00:08:55.953
Uh. hey. doc. uh. there's just
the one in there. right?

153
00:08:56.036 --> 00:08:58.413
- Are you serious right now?
- I'm-I'm just asking. all right.

154
00:08:58.497 --> 00:09:00.123
I've had enough surprises lately.

155
00:09:01.458 --> 00:09:03.377
What other surprises have you had?

156
00:09:04.962 --> 00:09:06.672
Well. isn't this enough?

157
00:09:07.965 --> 00:09:09.424
Feeling okay. Mr. Choi?

158
00:09:10.050 --> 00:09:11.301
Looking a bit pale.

159
00:09:11.385 --> 00:09:13.554
- [groans]
- [Grace] Yeah. you wanna lie down. hon?

160
00:09:13.637 --> 00:09:15.973
I know how exhausting
this must be for you.

161
00:09:17.432 --> 00:09:18.433
Thanks. I'm fine.

162
00:09:19.184 --> 00:09:22.479
Okay. So. music. Let's talk about it.

163
00:09:24.690 --> 00:09:26.149
What's music about for you guys?

164
00:09:28.443 --> 00:09:29.444
Um…

165
00:09:30.529 --> 00:09:33.532
Uh. think of the songs
that really made you feel something.

166
00:09:35.534 --> 00:09:38.787
Or what… The ones that really hit you.

167
00:09:40.581 --> 00:09:42.624
Why did they hit you
the way that they did?

168
00:09:43.208 --> 00:09:45.919
Was it the lyrics? Was it the melody?

169
00:09:46.420 --> 00:09:47.921
The rhythm? The bass?

170
00:09:48.005 --> 00:09:50.591
[chuckles] Come on. guys.
there's. like. no wrong answers here.

171
00:09:53.343 --> 00:09:54.386
[Ali chuckles]

172
00:09:58.056 --> 00:09:59.975
Yes. Yes. go ahead.

173
00:10:00.058 --> 00:10:02.436
Uh. you're supposed to be
teaching us chord progressions.

174
00:10:02.519 --> 00:10:03.896
Oh. yeah. Well. we'll get to that.

175
00:10:03.979 --> 00:10:09.943
I just… I don't want this class
to just be about music theory.

176
00:10:11.612 --> 00:10:13.488
I mean.
it's literally called Music Theory.

177
00:10:13.572 --> 00:10:14.823
Seriously?

178
00:10:14.907 --> 00:10:16.450
I mean. you do know
chord progressions. right?

179
00:10:16.533 --> 00:10:18.368
Yeah. of course I know chord progressions.

180
00:10:23.165 --> 00:10:24.166
Okay.

181
00:10:26.585 --> 00:10:29.880
How about a simple
1-4-5 chord progression in D major?

182
00:10:29.963 --> 00:10:32.216
Um. I will start.

183
00:10:32.299 --> 00:10:36.887
I'll play you the chords and then
you guys can play them back to me.

184
00:10:36.970 --> 00:10:38.222
Sound good?

185
00:10:38.847 --> 00:10:40.015
Cool. Okay. great.

186
00:10:40.098 --> 00:10:43.227
- So it starts on D.
- [guitar playing]

187
00:10:43.310 --> 00:10:45.354
- And then it goes to G.
- [guitar playing]

188
00:10:45.437 --> 00:10:47.272
Spying on your senior crush?

189
00:10:47.356 --> 00:10:48.440
Oh. hey.

190
00:10:50.317 --> 00:10:52.069
Oh. no. That's… That's my aunt.

191
00:10:52.152 --> 00:10:53.612
She got the gig?

192
00:10:53.695 --> 00:10:54.988
Yeah. it's her first day.

193
00:10:55.697 --> 00:10:56.698
Cool.

194
00:10:57.324 --> 00:10:59.409
So why are we spying on her?

195
00:11:00.160 --> 00:11:01.161
I-I'm not.

196
00:11:02.037 --> 00:11:04.831
I mean. it's. uh. a thing with Ali.

197
00:11:04.915 --> 00:11:06.959
She kind of marches to her own beat.

198
00:11:07.042 --> 00:11:08.293
So do you. right?

199
00:11:09.378 --> 00:11:11.547
[stammers] It's not
the same thing. [chuckles]

200
00:11:12.130 --> 00:11:14.508
I guess music runs in the family. huh?

201
00:11:14.591 --> 00:11:16.760
Not mine. My dad thinks he's a musician.

202
00:11:16.844 --> 00:11:19.179
but he thinks
he's a lot of things that he isn't.

203
00:11:19.930 --> 00:11:20.973
He seems pretty cool.

204
00:11:21.056 --> 00:11:22.558
Yeah? He's not.

205
00:11:29.565 --> 00:11:30.566
[Hunter] Hey.

206
00:11:35.529 --> 00:11:37.823
- You should come over sometime.
- Yeah?

207
00:11:37.906 --> 00:11:40.117
The house has this recording studio
in the basement.

208
00:11:40.200 --> 00:11:41.869
My dad outfitted the whole thing.

209
00:11:42.744 --> 00:11:44.496
- Cool. Yeah.
- So you'll come?

210
00:11:46.456 --> 00:11:48.333
Jesus. Hunter. it's just hanging out.

211
00:11:48.417 --> 00:11:49.877
It doesn't mean we're engaged.

212
00:11:50.627 --> 00:11:51.628
[both chuckle]

213
00:11:54.882 --> 00:11:56.758
The Wharton book. I need it back.

214
00:11:57.759 --> 00:11:59.511
Sure. Can I see your library card?

215
00:11:59.595 --> 00:12:01.096
Lu. come on.

216
00:12:01.180 --> 00:12:03.015
Why would you possibly need it back?

217
00:12:03.098 --> 00:12:04.516
Not me. the owner.

218
00:12:06.143 --> 00:12:07.936
You got caught.

219
00:12:08.020 --> 00:12:10.856
[sighs] Yeah.
it's a long story. but it's all good.

220
00:12:10.939 --> 00:12:13.275
I just… He just wants it back.

221
00:12:13.358 --> 00:12:14.860
Well. he can't have it.

222
00:12:14.943 --> 00:12:16.236
Why the hell not?

223
00:12:17.654 --> 00:12:19.907
There was a dog market in Buda only once.

224
00:12:21.533 --> 00:12:22.784
I don't know what that means.

225
00:12:22.868 --> 00:12:25.746
It means that's not how this works.

226
00:12:26.371 --> 00:12:28.207
The book's gone. Sold to a collector.

227
00:12:28.749 --> 00:12:30.792
What are you talking about?
You had it for. like. two days.

228
00:12:30.876 --> 00:12:32.794
I'm good at my job. Sue me.

229
00:12:32.878 --> 00:12:34.213
- Well. can you get it back?
- No.

230
00:12:34.296 --> 00:12:36.632
- Why not?
- Because that is not how this works.

231
00:12:36.715 --> 00:12:39.134
- Yeah. you said that already.
- Apparently it bears repeating.

232
00:12:39.718 --> 00:12:41.386
Well. can you put me in touch
with the buyer?

233
00:12:41.970 --> 00:12:43.722
[chuckling] You are kidding. right?

234
00:12:44.431 --> 00:12:46.975
You got caught. Coop.
You think I want any part of that?

235
00:12:47.059 --> 00:12:48.685
Lu. come on.
If I don't get that book back.

236
00:12:48.769 --> 00:12:49.978
he's gonna call the cops.

237
00:12:50.062 --> 00:12:51.813
Nah. Just make another deal with him.

238
00:12:51.897 --> 00:12:53.565
No. that's not how this works.

239
00:12:57.194 --> 00:12:58.820
Please. Lu. Please.

240
00:13:02.991 --> 00:13:03.992
[sighs]

241
00:13:05.118 --> 00:13:07.204
I'll make the call.
but that's all I can do.

242
00:13:07.287 --> 00:13:08.789
- [sighs]
- How much is in there?

243
00:13:08.872 --> 00:13:10.457
The hundred grand you gave me for it.

244
00:13:10.541 --> 00:13:13.085
That's not gonna cut it.
I sold it for two.

245
00:13:13.168 --> 00:13:15.379
It's called turning a profit.
Mr. Money Whiz.

246
00:13:15.462 --> 00:13:18.090
[sighs] I don't have
$200.000 lying around.

247
00:13:18.173 --> 00:13:20.050
You're probably gonna need
closer to three.

248
00:13:20.133 --> 00:13:23.136
- Jesus Christ.
- Like I said. good at my job.

249
00:13:24.012 --> 00:13:25.222
At least one of us is.

250
00:13:27.391 --> 00:13:29.685
Whenever you're ready. Action!

251
00:13:29.768 --> 00:13:33.230
I'm your man Nick Brandes.
and this is Off Brandes.

252
00:13:33.313 --> 00:13:35.482
The Triple Double's
latest greatest segment

253
00:13:35.566 --> 00:13:39.820
where we rank the biggest air balls
of the week on and off the court.

254
00:13:39.903 --> 00:13:41.947
If anyone's had
an off-brand moment… [chuckles]

255
00:13:42.030 --> 00:13:43.323
I'm here for it.

256
00:13:43.407 --> 00:13:45.784
- Let's go.
- [crowd cheering]

257
00:13:48.620 --> 00:13:50.372
All right. A-cam.
make sure you follow him.

258
00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:54.293
- [crowd groans]
- He's on fire. man.

259
00:13:54.376 --> 00:13:56.086
[cheering. chanting]

260
00:13:57.296 --> 00:13:58.297
[groans]

261
00:13:58.380 --> 00:14:00.465
[cheering]

262
00:14:02.509 --> 00:14:04.178
When he goes for the spin.
try and go in close.

263
00:14:10.851 --> 00:14:13.604
- Yeah. it's gonna look sick!
- Okay. that's a wrap.

264
00:14:14.813 --> 00:14:16.273
[Barney] You missed the walk-through.

265
00:14:16.356 --> 00:14:18.025
Shit. That was today?

266
00:14:18.108 --> 00:14:20.652
- Yeah. it's been on your calendar…
- [sighs]

267
00:14:20.736 --> 00:14:22.446
…long before this shoot was.

268
00:14:24.239 --> 00:14:26.992
This gym expansion
has to be a priority. Nick.

269
00:14:27.075 --> 00:14:28.619
Your people should have checked with me.

270
00:14:28.702 --> 00:14:30.370
No. no. it's-it's on me.

271
00:14:30.454 --> 00:14:32.664
With escrow closing on the new house
and now the show.

272
00:14:32.748 --> 00:14:34.416
I haven't been paying attention. I…

273
00:14:34.499 --> 00:14:36.585
[sighs] Sorry.

274
00:14:36.668 --> 00:14:39.546
Hey. never apologize for working hard.

275
00:14:40.047 --> 00:14:41.089
All right?

276
00:14:41.173 --> 00:14:42.758
Former athletes have a window.

277
00:14:42.841 --> 00:14:44.051
You're in yours.

278
00:14:45.677 --> 00:14:48.931
You can't be expected to
be across every detail of your business.

279
00:14:49.014 --> 00:14:50.015
That's why you pay me.

280
00:14:50.933 --> 00:14:52.059
Power of attorney?

281
00:14:53.060 --> 00:14:55.437
Yeah. yeah. It's just so
I can keep the gyms on track

282
00:14:55.521 --> 00:14:57.981
while you're becoming America's
most beloved sports personality.

283
00:14:58.065 --> 00:14:59.316
Ah. [chuckles]

284
00:14:59.399 --> 00:15:02.152
- Should I have my lawyer review this?
- I already sent it over to Doug.

285
00:15:02.236 --> 00:15:04.071
It's boilerplate. He's fine with it.

286
00:15:04.154 --> 00:15:05.364
You got a pen?

287
00:15:05.447 --> 00:15:06.448
Oh. okay.

288
00:15:14.915 --> 00:15:16.250
Uh. everything okay?

289
00:15:16.333 --> 00:15:18.210
Yeah. yeah. yeah. Why wouldn't it be?

290
00:15:18.293 --> 00:15:20.879
Uh. I don't know.
You just seem kind of nervous.

291
00:15:21.713 --> 00:15:22.923
I'm always nervous. Nick.

292
00:15:23.006 --> 00:15:24.591
No. more than usual I mean.

293
00:15:24.675 --> 00:15:25.676
[chuckles]

294
00:15:29.263 --> 00:15:30.848
Well. actually. uh…

295
00:15:31.849 --> 00:15:32.891
Grace is pregnant.

296
00:15:35.310 --> 00:15:37.396
- Get the fuck out of here.
- [chuckling] Yeah.

297
00:15:37.479 --> 00:15:38.689
- You serious?
- I am.

298
00:15:38.772 --> 00:15:40.566
- [chuckling] Congrats. my man.
- Oh. thanks.

299
00:15:40.649 --> 00:15:41.859
Thank you… Thank you.

300
00:15:41.942 --> 00:15:43.527
Oh. I thought you were
getting yourself snipped.

301
00:15:43.610 --> 00:15:45.112
[chuckles] I was. I was.

302
00:15:45.195 --> 00:15:46.738
- Um. I missed the appointment.
- Mm-hmm.

303
00:15:46.822 --> 00:15:49.199
And I hadn't gotten around
to rescheduling it yet. so…

304
00:15:49.283 --> 00:15:50.284
- Okay.
- Yeah.

305
00:15:50.367 --> 00:15:53.829
- [both chuckle]
- Well. uh. fuck it. let's toast.

306
00:15:53.912 --> 00:15:55.205
Okay. yeah.

307
00:15:56.540 --> 00:15:58.625
[Nick] Here we go for you.

308
00:15:58.709 --> 00:16:02.296
That is two. and three kids.

309
00:16:02.379 --> 00:16:03.380
- You…
- [chuckling] Yeah.

310
00:16:03.463 --> 00:16:05.424
Yep. I know that's an accident.

311
00:16:05.507 --> 00:16:06.592
[both chuckle]

312
00:16:06.675 --> 00:16:07.843
But you know what?

313
00:16:08.802 --> 00:16:10.179
To happy accidents.

314
00:16:13.765 --> 00:16:15.934
- [retches]
- Hmm? What?

315
00:16:16.018 --> 00:16:19.104
What… What the hell is that? [grunts]

316
00:16:19.188 --> 00:16:21.023
- That's my next endorsement deal.
- [grunts]

317
00:16:21.106 --> 00:16:23.859
It's called. uh.
Straight Shot Nonalcoholic Whiskey.

318
00:16:25.694 --> 00:16:27.029
That's a terrible idea.

319
00:16:28.697 --> 00:16:30.032
Have you already committed?

320
00:16:30.115 --> 00:16:31.450
- Not yet.
- Don't.

321
00:16:31.533 --> 00:16:34.494
[stammers] Why not? Y-You get
the experience without the poison.

322
00:16:34.578 --> 00:16:35.996
Nick… [inhales heavily]

323
00:16:36.079 --> 00:16:38.999
…the poison is the experience. okay?

324
00:16:41.460 --> 00:16:42.628
[Mel] Tor?

325
00:16:42.711 --> 00:16:43.962
In here.

326
00:16:44.046 --> 00:16:45.255
[Mel] You're home.

327
00:16:47.799 --> 00:16:49.218
What does that smell like to you?

328
00:16:49.801 --> 00:16:51.720
- Ew. Mom.
- It smells like dog piss.

329
00:16:51.803 --> 00:16:52.971
[Tori] Yeah.

330
00:16:53.055 --> 00:16:55.140
[Mel] I'm gonna kill that damn dog.

331
00:16:55.224 --> 00:16:56.350
Nice. Mom.

332
00:16:56.433 --> 00:16:58.185
Well. I don't mean literally.

333
00:17:00.395 --> 00:17:01.396
[Mel sighs]

334
00:17:02.731 --> 00:17:04.107
Why are you all dressed up?

335
00:17:05.483 --> 00:17:06.484
Am I?

336
00:17:15.160 --> 00:17:18.497
So. listen. and please don't be mad.

337
00:17:18.579 --> 00:17:19.873
Not a great start.

338
00:17:20.582 --> 00:17:21.916
[chuckles]

339
00:17:23.001 --> 00:17:26.088
I was able to make some calls.

340
00:17:26.839 --> 00:17:29.466
and Princeton is still on the table.

341
00:17:31.301 --> 00:17:32.302
I'm sorry. what?

342
00:17:34.137 --> 00:17:36.014
I got them to reject your rejection.

343
00:17:39.768 --> 00:17:41.979
- Un-fucking-believable.
- It doesn't mean you have to go.

344
00:17:42.062 --> 00:17:44.189
- It just means you have options.
- You don't know when to stop.

345
00:17:44.273 --> 00:17:45.566
And options are good.

346
00:17:46.984 --> 00:17:47.985
Okay.

347
00:17:49.194 --> 00:17:50.404
I'll just decline again.

348
00:17:54.241 --> 00:17:56.785
Not unless that's the last time
you want to see your phone.

349
00:17:58.036 --> 00:17:59.079
I'm 18. Mom.

350
00:17:59.162 --> 00:18:00.789
- And on the family plan.
- Dad's plan.

351
00:18:00.873 --> 00:18:02.374
He feels the same way I do.

352
00:18:03.166 --> 00:18:04.793
Right. well. this is my life.

353
00:18:08.088 --> 00:18:10.132
Then why don't you tell me
what you wanna do with it?

354
00:18:10.215 --> 00:18:12.259
I want to figure it out for myself.

355
00:18:14.011 --> 00:18:16.013
I know that technically you're an adult.

356
00:18:16.513 --> 00:18:18.932
but your prefrontal cortex
is not fully developed

357
00:18:19.016 --> 00:18:20.642
until you're about 26 years old. so--

358
00:18:20.726 --> 00:18:21.977
Don't-- Okay. don't do that.

359
00:18:22.060 --> 00:18:25.522
- You are not my therapist.
- No. but I see plenty of kids your age.

360
00:18:25.606 --> 00:18:26.857
Not anymore you don't.

361
00:18:30.360 --> 00:18:31.945
What do you even do all day?

362
00:18:33.822 --> 00:18:36.533
I don't think it's me
you're really mad at.

363
00:18:36.617 --> 00:18:38.452
Yeah. no. it's a hundred-percent you.

364
00:18:38.535 --> 00:18:41.371
Oh. I told Daddy you were doing this
to punish both of us.

365
00:18:41.455 --> 00:18:44.166
I… I guess I was wrong.
I guess it's just me.

366
00:18:45.125 --> 00:18:46.126
Right.

367
00:18:47.044 --> 00:18:49.671
Or have you considered
the mind-blowing possibility

368
00:18:49.755 --> 00:18:51.465
that not everything is about you?

369
00:18:51.548 --> 00:18:53.675
You just told me it was 100% about me.

370
00:18:53.759 --> 00:18:56.803
God. Jesus Christ. Mom.
That was about not respecting my choices.

371
00:18:56.887 --> 00:19:00.224
Oh. my God. I am trying so hard
not to disrespect your choices.

372
00:19:00.307 --> 00:19:02.226
Good. Because I think you lost that right

373
00:19:02.309 --> 00:19:05.270
when you chose to attack
your husband's ex-lover and get fired.

374
00:19:06.563 --> 00:19:09.650
You keep trying to shove me
into making the same decisions you made.

375
00:19:09.733 --> 00:19:11.235
but I look at you.

376
00:19:11.318 --> 00:19:14.279
and all I can think is why the fuck
would I wanna be like you?

377
00:19:14.363 --> 00:19:16.031
[somber music playing]

378
00:19:38.262 --> 00:19:42.933
- Surprise! [cheering]
- ["Mueve La Cadera" playing on speakers]

379
00:19:43.725 --> 00:19:45.853
[in Spanish] You trying to give me
a heart attack or what?

380
00:19:45.936 --> 00:19:47.896
That's what you get
for letting me sleep on your couch.

381
00:19:47.980 --> 00:19:50.274
Give it up for our brand new gringa!

382
00:19:50.357 --> 00:19:52.317
- [chuckles]
- [cheering continues]

383
00:19:55.028 --> 00:19:56.029
Let's dance!

384
00:20:05.330 --> 00:20:08.917
[chanting]

385
00:20:12.880 --> 00:20:13.881
[in English] Hey.

386
00:20:17.176 --> 00:20:18.177
What?

387
00:20:19.469 --> 00:20:20.637
You look terrible.

388
00:20:20.721 --> 00:20:21.930
- Okay. Careful.
- [chuckling]

389
00:20:22.014 --> 00:20:24.808
- A lot of people end up dead around me.
- Now I gotta watch myself. don't I?

390
00:20:24.892 --> 00:20:26.768
- Which shithole are you taking me to?
- Martine's.

391
00:20:26.852 --> 00:20:28.812
Supposed to be the hottest place in town.

392
00:20:28.896 --> 00:20:29.897
What? Was that a mistake?

393
00:20:29.980 --> 00:20:31.899
[stammers] I'm just trying
to keep a low profile.

394
00:20:31.982 --> 00:20:34.193
- Oh. right. You're embarrassed of me.
- Martine's is very…

395
00:20:34.276 --> 00:20:35.360
- What? No.
- I'm joking.

396
00:20:35.444 --> 00:20:36.945
Come on. Sam. I get it. You were shunned.

397
00:20:37.029 --> 00:20:38.697
- Shunned is a strong word.
- And you don't wanna

398
00:20:38.780 --> 00:20:41.450
- walk right into the belly of the beast.
- I like "persona non grata." Exactly.

399
00:20:41.533 --> 00:20:42.993
- I know just the place.
- Great.

400
00:20:50.834 --> 00:20:52.211
[engine revving]

401
00:20:55.547 --> 00:20:56.965
[phone buzzing]

402
00:21:00.219 --> 00:21:01.220
Lu?

403
00:21:01.303 --> 00:21:02.888
[Lu] The buyer's agreed to meet.

404
00:21:02.971 --> 00:21:05.807
Lunch tomorrow. I'll send you the address.

405
00:21:05.891 --> 00:21:06.892
Okay. great.

406
00:21:06.975 --> 00:21:08.894
- Thank you.
- You wanna thank me?

407
00:21:09.603 --> 00:21:10.812
Don't look like an amateur.

408
00:21:10.896 --> 00:21:13.482
If you look like an amateur.
I look like an amateur.

409
00:21:14.650 --> 00:21:15.776
Okay.

410
00:21:15.859 --> 00:21:18.654
It's not okay.
I have a reputation to worry about.

411
00:21:20.489 --> 00:21:22.157
Coop. you there?

412
00:21:22.241 --> 00:21:25.827
Yeah. I'm here.
Don't look like an amateur. got it.

413
00:21:25.911 --> 00:21:27.037
You got the cash?

414
00:21:28.622 --> 00:21:29.623
I'm about to.

415
00:21:30.374 --> 00:21:31.708
God help us.

416
00:21:31.792 --> 00:21:34.545
Hey. listen. I know this isn't
just business as usual for you.

417
00:21:34.628 --> 00:21:37.548
so I just wanted to say thank you
and I really apprecia…

418
00:21:39.508 --> 00:21:41.009
You're gone. aren't you?

419
00:21:42.094 --> 00:21:43.303
- She's not there.
- [phone thuds]

420
00:21:47.766 --> 00:21:49.351
- Hey.
- [Elena] Hi.

421
00:21:49.852 --> 00:21:51.854
- Congratulations.
- Oh. thank you.

422
00:21:51.937 --> 00:21:53.897
[both chuckle]

423
00:21:53.981 --> 00:21:55.148
- [Coop] Goodness.
- Aw.

424
00:21:55.232 --> 00:21:56.650
- How does it feel?
- Oh. I don't know.

425
00:21:56.733 --> 00:21:58.777
Like… it's nice
to finally feel like I belong.

426
00:21:58.861 --> 00:22:01.113
- You know?
- Yes. Ooh. I got you something.

427
00:22:03.824 --> 00:22:05.868
[Elena] Oh. shut up.

428
00:22:05.951 --> 00:22:08.871
[chuckling] No. I told you
not to steal one of these for me.

429
00:22:08.954 --> 00:22:10.789
Come on. I wouldn't steal a gift.

430
00:22:10.873 --> 00:22:14.042
I bought it at the store like a person.

431
00:22:20.257 --> 00:22:22.009
You went to Cartier for me?

432
00:22:26.889 --> 00:22:28.557
Well. it's very basic rich bitch.

433
00:22:28.640 --> 00:22:31.685
[laughs] Well. there's a gift receipt
in the box if you wanna exchange it.

434
00:22:31.768 --> 00:22:32.895
I would never.

435
00:22:36.440 --> 00:22:37.983
- Thanks. Coop.
- Aw.

436
00:22:38.066 --> 00:22:39.443
This means the world.

437
00:22:40.444 --> 00:22:41.570
So now what?

438
00:22:41.653 --> 00:22:44.781
Well. I'm already working on
getting my parents here.

439
00:22:44.865 --> 00:22:46.325
I even hired a lawyer and everything.

440
00:22:46.408 --> 00:22:47.784
That's terrific. Good for you.

441
00:22:47.868 --> 00:22:50.829
I just have to prove that I make
enough money to support them both.

442
00:22:50.913 --> 00:22:53.332
which is not gonna happen
on my housekeeper salary.

443
00:22:53.415 --> 00:22:58.295
So I'm still very much into doing
the thing that we're definitely not doing.

444
00:23:00.506 --> 00:23:02.174
I'm gonna need every dime I can get.

445
00:23:04.510 --> 00:23:08.138
Well. speaking of. uh.
I think Barney's got us sorted out.

446
00:23:08.722 --> 00:23:09.723
Really?

447
00:23:10.224 --> 00:23:13.727
Can you explain to me again how my money
is gonna grow in Nick's gyms?

448
00:23:14.937 --> 00:23:16.605
- No. not really.
- [laughs]

449
00:23:16.688 --> 00:23:20.192
In fact. it will probably get smaller.
but at least it will look legit…

450
00:23:20.275 --> 00:23:22.027
- [groans. sighs]
- …according to the IRS.

451
00:23:22.110 --> 00:23:23.529
Fucking America. man.

452
00:23:24.238 --> 00:23:25.364
Tell me about it.

453
00:23:28.742 --> 00:23:30.619
- So. what's up?
- What are you talking about?

454
00:23:32.037 --> 00:23:33.872
You didn't come all this way
just to give me this.

455
00:23:33.956 --> 00:23:35.040
Come on.

456
00:23:41.129 --> 00:23:43.340
How many times do you
become a United States citizen?

457
00:23:43.841 --> 00:23:46.009
- [laughs]
- I figured it was worth the drive.

458
00:23:48.595 --> 00:23:49.930
Don't get soft on me now. Coop.

459
00:23:50.013 --> 00:23:51.431
Oh. that's not gonna happen.

460
00:23:56.186 --> 00:23:57.646
Okay. I'm gonna go back in.

461
00:23:57.729 --> 00:23:59.273
Okay. enjoy yourself.

462
00:23:59.773 --> 00:24:01.400
- Thanks again.
- You're welcome.

463
00:24:06.780 --> 00:24:09.116
[exhales deeply]

464
00:24:11.159 --> 00:24:14.162
- You take all your dates here?
- [chuckles] Uh…

465
00:24:14.246 --> 00:24:17.124
historically. the women I've dated
would probably not appreciate

466
00:24:17.207 --> 00:24:19.585
the pleasures of a pizza joint.

467
00:24:19.668 --> 00:24:21.128
You need to date different people.

468
00:24:21.211 --> 00:24:23.422
- Yeah. I'm trying. Cheers.
- Mmm. [laughs]

469
00:24:24.047 --> 00:24:25.257
- Cheers.
- Mmm.

470
00:24:26.258 --> 00:24:28.177
All right. So tell me about yourself.

471
00:24:28.260 --> 00:24:29.261
Where are you from?

472
00:24:29.344 --> 00:24:30.596
South Boston.

473
00:24:30.679 --> 00:24:32.431
- Wow. really? A Southie?
- Mm-hmm.

474
00:24:32.514 --> 00:24:33.807
How'd you lose the accent?

475
00:24:33.891 --> 00:24:37.561
Years of practicing in front of the mirror
trying to sound like Molly Ringwald.

476
00:24:37.644 --> 00:24:39.980
[laughing]

477
00:24:40.063 --> 00:24:41.648
- You were driven.
- I was.

478
00:24:41.732 --> 00:24:43.317
Booked it out of there as fast as I could.

479
00:24:44.193 --> 00:24:46.028
Yeah. but it stays with you. doesn't it?

480
00:24:46.111 --> 00:24:48.906
I mean. no matter how much money I make.
the Westmonts of the world

481
00:24:48.989 --> 00:24:50.866
always make me feel like
the kid with the stinky lunch.

482
00:24:50.949 --> 00:24:52.492
[groans] Tell me about it.

483
00:24:52.576 --> 00:24:56.038
I thought I was in. and then. you know.
one wrong move and I'm out again.

484
00:24:56.121 --> 00:24:57.623
Yeah. one wrong move.

485
00:24:57.706 --> 00:25:00.125
- Yeah. well. [laughs]
- Well. that's a spectacular undersell.

486
00:25:00.209 --> 00:25:02.211
It's not like you used
the wrong fork for your salad.

487
00:25:02.294 --> 00:25:04.463
Look. I'm not saying I don't deserve it.

488
00:25:04.546 --> 00:25:06.006
Mistakes were made.

489
00:25:06.632 --> 00:25:08.967
You know. I was… I was under duress.

490
00:25:09.843 --> 00:25:11.512
Is that an explanation or an excuse?

491
00:25:12.179 --> 00:25:13.680
Can it be both?

492
00:25:13.764 --> 00:25:15.057
Whatever gets me the second date.

493
00:25:16.266 --> 00:25:19.770
- [server] All right. here you go.
- Oh. you are not ready for this.

494
00:25:19.853 --> 00:25:20.896
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

495
00:25:20.979 --> 00:25:22.105
All right.

496
00:25:22.689 --> 00:25:23.815
After you.

497
00:25:28.612 --> 00:25:30.280
- Oh. my God.
- How fucking good is that?

498
00:25:30.364 --> 00:25:31.532
- Oh. my God.
- Right?

499
00:25:31.615 --> 00:25:33.200
My work takes me all over the world.

500
00:25:33.283 --> 00:25:35.994
And everywhere I go. I always find
a little hole-in-the-wall pizza joint

501
00:25:36.078 --> 00:25:37.412
'cause they always have the best slices.

502
00:25:37.496 --> 00:25:41.124
Speaking of which.
you haven't told me what it is you do.

503
00:25:41.959 --> 00:25:42.960
Yeah. it's boring.

504
00:25:43.544 --> 00:25:46.255
Also. in European culture.
it's considered gauche to even ask.

505
00:25:46.338 --> 00:25:47.840
Mmm. well. we're in Westchester.

506
00:25:47.923 --> 00:25:49.550
- so you're shit out of luck.
- [laughs]

507
00:25:50.259 --> 00:25:51.510
I own a shipping company.

508
00:25:54.179 --> 00:25:55.556
- Would you like to elaborate?
- [laughs]

509
00:25:55.639 --> 00:25:57.391
What is it that you do
with the shipping company?

510
00:25:57.474 --> 00:25:59.685
- We have… We have container ships…
- Mm-hmm.

511
00:25:59.768 --> 00:26:02.020
…and we move merchandise
from point A to point B.

512
00:26:03.772 --> 00:26:05.399
- That's it?
- That's it.

513
00:26:05.482 --> 00:26:06.608
- That's it?
- Mm-hmm.

514
00:26:06.692 --> 00:26:08.443
- That's it?
- It's exciting. right?

515
00:26:08.944 --> 00:26:11.196
- You have so much money.
- I have a lot of ships.

516
00:26:11.280 --> 00:26:12.781
[both laugh]

517
00:26:12.865 --> 00:26:15.951
Okay. so you're either being evasive.
or it really is that boring.

518
00:26:16.827 --> 00:26:17.828
Can it be both?

519
00:26:17.911 --> 00:26:19.204
Mmm. touché.

520
00:26:19.288 --> 00:26:20.497
All right. Enough about me.

521
00:26:20.581 --> 00:26:21.915
- Walk me through it.
- Mmm.

522
00:26:21.999 --> 00:26:25.919
How does the hottest girl in South Boston
end up in Westmont Village?

523
00:26:26.003 --> 00:26:28.672
Mmm. You know. I wasn't
the hottest girl in South Boston.

524
00:26:28.755 --> 00:26:30.299
- That was Heather Burns.
- Come on.

525
00:26:30.382 --> 00:26:32.217
- Heather Burns. Mmm.
- Yes. Heather Burns.

526
00:26:32.301 --> 00:26:33.468
Where is she now?

527
00:26:33.552 --> 00:26:35.554
- Still there. teaching middle school.
- Yeah?

528
00:26:35.637 --> 00:26:37.306
- Oh. respect. Okay.
- Mm-hmm.

529
00:26:37.389 --> 00:26:39.683
- How's she looking?
- She is still hot.

530
00:26:39.766 --> 00:26:41.810
- Would you like her number?
- You're just being nice. No. no.

531
00:26:41.894 --> 00:26:44.188
I just wanna know if everybody
from South Boston looks like you.

532
00:26:44.271 --> 00:26:45.981
We could drive there right now.

533
00:26:47.482 --> 00:26:49.651
[Ali coughs] Oh. God.

534
00:26:55.365 --> 00:26:56.742
These fucking kids.

535
00:26:57.743 --> 00:27:00.037
They sit there like fucking robots.

536
00:27:00.120 --> 00:27:04.583
They got no energy.
no engagement. no excitement.

537
00:27:06.293 --> 00:27:09.755
I think the job is less
me teaching the music

538
00:27:09.838 --> 00:27:12.674
and more just trying to get them
to give a shit.

539
00:27:12.758 --> 00:27:13.800
[sighs]

540
00:27:14.635 --> 00:27:16.720
Well. if anybody can do that. you can.

541
00:27:16.803 --> 00:27:18.639
Oh. says the guy
who thinks I can't hack it.

542
00:27:22.351 --> 00:27:23.810
I thought you forgave me for that.

543
00:27:24.311 --> 00:27:26.104
- [people on TV chattering]
- I did.

544
00:27:26.772 --> 00:27:28.482
But it doesn't mean
you stopped thinking it.

545
00:27:29.399 --> 00:27:30.526
I don't know what I think.

546
00:27:30.609 --> 00:27:31.944
This is some strong shit. man.

547
00:27:32.027 --> 00:27:33.570
[sighs] It's medical grade.

548
00:27:40.994 --> 00:27:44.915
There was this study done at Harvard
where they took a bunch of ordinary rats.

549
00:27:44.998 --> 00:27:48.710
and they separated them arbitrarily
into two different cages.

550
00:27:48.794 --> 00:27:50.629
And then they labeled the cages.

551
00:27:50.712 --> 00:27:55.259
One they labeled "really smart"
and the other they labeled "dumb as shit."

552
00:27:55.342 --> 00:27:57.553
They wrote "dumb as shit"
on a cage at Harvard?

553
00:27:57.636 --> 00:27:59.096
[sighs] The point is.

554
00:28:00.472 --> 00:28:03.308
then they took a bunch of students.

555
00:28:03.392 --> 00:28:06.728
and they had the students
take a rat from each cage.

556
00:28:06.812 --> 00:28:08.772
and they had the rats run a maze.

557
00:28:08.856 --> 00:28:10.065
And do you know what happened?

558
00:28:11.358 --> 00:28:13.861
- The "dumb as shit" ones couldn't do it.
- That's right.

559
00:28:13.944 --> 00:28:15.988
The rats were all exactly the same.

560
00:28:16.572 --> 00:28:20.117
But because of the labels.
the students had expectations of them.

561
00:28:20.200 --> 00:28:22.995
and so the rats
lived up to those expectations.

562
00:28:24.913 --> 00:28:26.081
Why are we talking about this?

563
00:28:27.958 --> 00:28:29.501
Because I am the rat.

564
00:28:31.003 --> 00:28:32.880
And if you think I'm gonna fail. I'm…

565
00:28:33.922 --> 00:28:35.799
Probably will.

566
00:28:35.883 --> 00:28:37.676
[downcast music playing]

567
00:28:42.014 --> 00:28:43.182
Anyway.

568
00:28:43.265 --> 00:28:44.308
[groans]

569
00:28:47.227 --> 00:28:50.981
Maybe it's time you let me
find my way out of the maze by myself.

570
00:28:51.064 --> 00:28:53.525
[door opens. closes]

571
00:28:55.611 --> 00:28:57.362
Tori. hey.

572
00:28:57.446 --> 00:28:59.072
I can't with Mom. I'm moving in.

573
00:28:59.698 --> 00:29:01.783
[footsteps departing]

574
00:29:04.328 --> 00:29:05.746
You saw her too. right?

575
00:29:06.288 --> 00:29:08.040
[determined music playing]

576
00:29:13.837 --> 00:29:15.714
[Coop] First my back went out.

577
00:29:15.797 --> 00:29:17.424
Then I got caught red-handed.

578
00:29:17.925 --> 00:29:20.302
Now I had pawned something
for 100.000 bucks

579
00:29:20.385 --> 00:29:23.055
that I would have to buy back
for twice that. at minimum.

580
00:29:23.639 --> 00:29:26.308
It was all putting
a serious dent in my pride.

581
00:29:26.391 --> 00:29:27.893
Not to mention my cash flow.

582
00:29:28.894 --> 00:29:30.062
And the irony was.

583
00:29:30.145 --> 00:29:32.981
I would have to hit multiple houses
at the exact moment

584
00:29:33.065 --> 00:29:35.692
I was starting to wonder
if I was even any good at it.

585
00:29:36.610 --> 00:29:37.611
Right this way. sir.

586
00:29:42.449 --> 00:29:43.450
What the fuck?

587
00:29:46.328 --> 00:29:47.329
Ashe?

588
00:29:47.412 --> 00:29:49.498
[laughs] Surprised?

589
00:29:51.041 --> 00:29:52.292
Surprised is a word.

590
00:29:53.377 --> 00:29:54.378
I'm the buyer.

591
00:29:56.964 --> 00:29:57.965
What?

592
00:29:58.048 --> 00:29:59.049
[server 2] Bon appétit.

593
00:29:59.758 --> 00:30:02.010
Mmm. You have to try this crudo. man.

594
00:30:02.094 --> 00:30:03.095
It's fucking insane.

595
00:30:04.346 --> 00:30:05.889
You bought your own book back?

596
00:30:05.973 --> 00:30:07.975
Yeah. I told you. It means a lot to me.

597
00:30:08.851 --> 00:30:10.435
How did you track it down?

598
00:30:11.395 --> 00:30:14.356
Well. the hot books market's
not really a large one.

599
00:30:14.439 --> 00:30:18.193
So. this whole idea of me chasing around
trying to find it. that was just for fun?

600
00:30:18.277 --> 00:30:19.570
Exactly. Team building.

601
00:30:19.653 --> 00:30:22.239
Okay. Well. no harm. no foul.

602
00:30:23.031 --> 00:30:24.741
Um… [laughs] …wait.

603
00:30:24.825 --> 00:30:26.451
I'm still out 200 grand.

604
00:30:26.535 --> 00:30:28.745
Yeah. Here's 150.

605
00:30:28.829 --> 00:30:30.330
Give me another week.
I'll get you the rest.

606
00:30:30.414 --> 00:30:32.499
How you gonna do that?
You gonna rob somebody else?

607
00:30:33.333 --> 00:30:35.169
- [sighs]
- Come on.

608
00:30:36.044 --> 00:30:37.254
I got a better idea.

609
00:30:37.880 --> 00:30:38.881
Sit down.

610
00:30:42.342 --> 00:30:43.343
Okay. look.

611
00:30:43.969 --> 00:30:47.014
I'm looking to move some money
into a hedge fund.

612
00:30:47.097 --> 00:30:48.974
Or establish a position.
or however the fuck you say it.

613
00:30:49.057 --> 00:30:51.059
Yeah. well. I'm not really
in that business anymore.

614
00:30:51.143 --> 00:30:52.686
but I can introduce you to some guys who--

615
00:30:52.769 --> 00:30:54.188
It's a Bailey Russell fund.

616
00:30:55.689 --> 00:30:57.274
- You're talking about Excelsior.
- Mmm.

617
00:30:57.357 --> 00:30:58.942
Excelsior is Jack Bailey's baby.

618
00:30:59.026 --> 00:31:01.445
He runs it and he pretty much hates me.

619
00:31:01.528 --> 00:31:03.614
Well. you're gonna be coming in
with 400 million bucks.

620
00:31:03.697 --> 00:31:06.074
- so I think he'll get over it.
- [scoffs]

621
00:31:06.158 --> 00:31:08.577
If you're investing $400 million.
you don't need me.

622
00:31:09.161 --> 00:31:12.164
You'll be fighting off every firm
in town with a stick.

623
00:31:12.247 --> 00:31:15.792
I'm sure you're familiar with
the Office of Foreign Assets Control.

624
00:31:15.876 --> 00:31:17.002
OFAC. yes.

625
00:31:21.006 --> 00:31:23.133
How the fuck did you get on the OFAC list?

626
00:31:23.217 --> 00:31:26.094
I ship cargo all over the world.

627
00:31:26.178 --> 00:31:27.596
And let's just say the US Government

628
00:31:27.679 --> 00:31:29.640
is not on speaking terms
with some of my clients.

629
00:31:29.723 --> 00:31:31.225
- And the new administration…
- [scoffs]

630
00:31:31.308 --> 00:31:32.809
…has a big. fat hard-on for me.

631
00:31:33.519 --> 00:31:36.939
My assets. such as they are.
are vulnerable to seizure.

632
00:31:37.564 --> 00:31:39.441
So I have to diversify quickly.

633
00:31:39.525 --> 00:31:40.943
You can't ask me to do that.

634
00:31:41.026 --> 00:31:43.278
- I'm not asking.
- It's against the law.

635
00:31:43.362 --> 00:31:44.696
You robbed my house.

636
00:31:44.780 --> 00:31:46.031
This is different.

637
00:31:46.114 --> 00:31:47.824
- Yeah? I don't think it is.
- Well. listen.

638
00:31:47.908 --> 00:31:50.661
Even if I could get you
into Excelsior. which I cannot.

639
00:31:51.161 --> 00:31:54.081
there is no way
that your money clears compliance.

640
00:31:54.790 --> 00:31:56.959
- You're saying you can't do it?
- I'm saying no one can.

641
00:31:58.293 --> 00:32:00.254
You don't become what you want.

642
00:32:00.879 --> 00:32:02.297
You become what you believe.

643
00:32:03.924 --> 00:32:05.008
Oprah said that.

644
00:32:05.092 --> 00:32:06.969
Good. Get her to manage your portfolio.

645
00:32:07.052 --> 00:32:08.095
Come on. Coop.

646
00:32:08.178 --> 00:32:09.763
There's 17.000 people on that list.

647
00:32:09.847 --> 00:32:12.432
You seriously expect me to believe
there's not one SDN investing

648
00:32:12.516 --> 00:32:13.559
in Bailey Russell funds?

649
00:32:17.312 --> 00:32:18.814
Look. man. It's a zero-sum game.

650
00:32:18.897 --> 00:32:21.775
You can help me out.
or you can get arrested…

651
00:32:22.484 --> 00:32:23.485
again.

652
00:32:23.569 --> 00:32:25.487
So now it's just straight blackmail?

653
00:32:25.571 --> 00:32:26.572
Look…

654
00:32:27.281 --> 00:32:28.532
we're driven men. you and I.

655
00:32:29.616 --> 00:32:31.159
We've worked hard for what is ours.

656
00:32:31.243 --> 00:32:33.245
and we'll do what
we have to do to keep it.

657
00:32:34.371 --> 00:32:35.622
So I know you get it.

658
00:32:37.416 --> 00:32:39.668
I'll give you 48 hours
to come up with a plan.

659
00:32:41.003 --> 00:32:42.629
Do you wanna split a chocolate cake?

660
00:32:42.713 --> 00:32:43.714
How are you with gluten?

661
00:32:43.797 --> 00:32:45.132
Can we get two forks. please?

662
00:32:45.215 --> 00:32:47.968
[Coop] There are moments in your life
that you regret in hindsight.

663
00:32:48.051 --> 00:32:50.679
And then there are the moments
you're already regretting

664
00:32:50.762 --> 00:32:52.556
even while they're still happening.

665
00:32:55.267 --> 00:32:57.811
I knew it was a bad idea
to get involved with Owen Ashe.

666
00:32:57.895 --> 00:33:00.022
but I couldn't see a way out of it.

667
00:33:00.606 --> 00:33:03.525
And if nothing else.
I had to marvel at my unrivaled ability

668
00:33:03.609 --> 00:33:07.112
to take a bad situation
and make it so much worse.

669
00:33:07.196 --> 00:33:08.989
[sighs]

670
00:33:12.117 --> 00:33:13.118
Beep.

671
00:33:14.244 --> 00:33:15.746
Lehayim.

672
00:33:17.539 --> 00:33:18.749
How's your new roommate?

673
00:33:20.417 --> 00:33:23.086
I'll let you know
once she starts talking to me.

674
00:33:23.962 --> 00:33:25.047
How are you?

675
00:33:26.340 --> 00:33:27.591
You know. I've been better.

676
00:33:28.509 --> 00:33:30.093
You know why she came to you. right?

677
00:33:31.053 --> 00:33:32.221
Because I'm her father.

678
00:33:32.930 --> 00:33:34.473
'Cause you're the vacation parent.

679
00:33:35.057 --> 00:33:36.183
The fun one.

680
00:33:36.892 --> 00:33:38.644
Okay. are you mad
because she's pissed at you.

681
00:33:38.727 --> 00:33:40.229
or because she came to me?

682
00:33:41.063 --> 00:33:42.439
- Seriously.
- You were always at work.

683
00:33:42.523 --> 00:33:44.566
I was the one who had to hold the line.

684
00:33:44.650 --> 00:33:47.236
You'd maybe emerge
for a couple of hours on weekends.

685
00:33:47.319 --> 00:33:48.612
but all bets were off.

686
00:33:49.238 --> 00:33:50.781
You never said no to her.

687
00:33:51.448 --> 00:33:53.450
Mmm. She was always so good.

688
00:33:53.951 --> 00:33:55.577
She was good because I was on it.

689
00:33:55.661 --> 00:33:58.705
"Brush your teeth. Drink your milk.
Do your homework. Be home by 11:00.

690
00:33:58.789 --> 00:34:00.624
Get off your screens.

691
00:34:00.707 --> 00:34:02.626
You can't leave the house
wearing that outfit."

692
00:34:03.544 --> 00:34:05.420
Whenever they came to you
for permission for something.

693
00:34:05.504 --> 00:34:07.673
you'd be like. "What did Mom say?"

694
00:34:07.756 --> 00:34:09.424
Yeah. 'cause I was backing you up.

695
00:34:09.507 --> 00:34:10.592
You were passing the buck.

696
00:34:10.676 --> 00:34:12.177
Oh. please.

697
00:34:14.179 --> 00:34:18.266
I gave everything I had to those kids.
and somehow I'm the asshole.

698
00:34:18.350 --> 00:34:19.976
Well. if the shoe fits.

699
00:34:21.562 --> 00:34:22.563
Come on.

700
00:34:22.646 --> 00:34:23.647
[scoffs]

701
00:34:24.815 --> 00:34:26.233
[sighs]

702
00:34:26.315 --> 00:34:28.235
Girls push back against their mothers.

703
00:34:28.318 --> 00:34:30.529
It's a thing. It'll pass.

704
00:34:31.947 --> 00:34:33.949
I guess you're just thrilled
you get her all to yourself.

705
00:34:34.032 --> 00:34:36.284
Well. it's not the worst.

706
00:34:37.619 --> 00:34:40.121
If I'm being honest.
my house can be a little lonely.

707
00:34:41.123 --> 00:34:43.958
I mean. I lived with you guys
for 18 years.

708
00:34:44.042 --> 00:34:47.379
It's honestly kind of nice
to have her slamming doors

709
00:34:47.462 --> 00:34:49.047
and rolling her eyes at me.

710
00:34:50.632 --> 00:34:51.675
Ain't it?

711
00:34:56.221 --> 00:34:58.140
[sighs] This will run its course. Mel.

712
00:34:59.641 --> 00:35:00.976
She's gonna need her mom.

713
00:35:02.769 --> 00:35:04.271
But she's gonna be gone soon.

714
00:35:05.689 --> 00:35:06.690
Yeah.

715
00:35:07.357 --> 00:35:09.651
Even if she doesn't go to college. she's…

716
00:35:11.778 --> 00:35:13.030
off on her way.

717
00:35:15.741 --> 00:35:17.492
God. it just doesn't seem that long ago

718
00:35:17.576 --> 00:35:19.620
we brought her home
from the hospital. does it?

719
00:35:21.038 --> 00:35:23.123
Yeah. I remember the hospital.

720
00:35:23.874 --> 00:35:26.168
You came to pick us up
and forgot where you parked.

721
00:35:26.251 --> 00:35:28.337
Well. I was a little bit stressed. It was…

722
00:35:28.420 --> 00:35:29.630
- Walking around…
- First kid.

723
00:35:29.713 --> 00:35:31.173
…the parking structure for an hour.

724
00:35:31.256 --> 00:35:32.966
- Twenty minutes. tops.
- Oh. [chuckles]

725
00:35:33.050 --> 00:35:35.469
God. you thought Tori
was gonna die of exposure.

726
00:35:35.552 --> 00:35:36.637
It was cold.

727
00:35:38.180 --> 00:35:39.515
No. it wasn't.

728
00:35:41.975 --> 00:35:43.185
First kid.

729
00:35:43.268 --> 00:35:44.311
Yeah.

730
00:35:45.145 --> 00:35:46.146
For sure.

731
00:35:52.444 --> 00:35:56.114
You have these kids. this family.
and it's your whole world.

732
00:35:56.198 --> 00:35:58.367
And then you realize everybody leaves.

733
00:36:00.953 --> 00:36:04.456
[sighs] First Tori's gonna go.
then Hunter and then…

734
00:36:07.167 --> 00:36:08.919
[sniffles] Who am I gonna be?

735
00:36:10.796 --> 00:36:13.674
Some lonely old hag living
in a big empty house.

736
00:36:17.302 --> 00:36:19.513
Well. I mean. if you wanna downsize.
we can talk about it.

737
00:36:19.596 --> 00:36:21.348
No fucking way. Get outta here.

738
00:36:30.065 --> 00:36:31.066
[sniffles]

739
00:36:33.110 --> 00:36:35.320
- How the hell did this happen?
- [chuckles]

740
00:36:37.531 --> 00:36:39.324
We were never supposed to get this old.

741
00:36:45.831 --> 00:36:47.124
We blinked.

742
00:36:55.924 --> 00:36:57.301
- Oh. hey…
- [sniffles]

743
00:36:58.844 --> 00:36:59.845
Not a big deal.

744
00:36:59.928 --> 00:37:05.851
but. uh. I just got a bill for $3.000
for something called a Mona Lisa?

745
00:37:05.934 --> 00:37:10.147
Oh. that is a skin treatment. It's…

746
00:37:11.148 --> 00:37:12.316
- All right.
- For your…

747
00:37:13.358 --> 00:37:14.359
Yeah.

748
00:37:15.736 --> 00:37:16.737
Smile.

749
00:37:18.530 --> 00:37:21.533
Yeah. everyone's mad on social media
complaining about ratings

750
00:37:21.617 --> 00:37:23.035
saying they want the '90s back.

751
00:37:23.118 --> 00:37:24.870
- And then those same folks complain…
- Whiskey.

752
00:37:24.953 --> 00:37:26.538
…as soon as they have to…

753
00:37:26.622 --> 00:37:28.165
- Hey.
- Hey.

754
00:37:28.248 --> 00:37:29.750
Hey. Look at that.

755
00:37:29.833 --> 00:37:32.544
Don't tell me the patron saint of flopping
is weighing in on this.

756
00:37:32.628 --> 00:37:34.713
[presenter] I know you're talking
to him and not me.

757
00:37:34.796 --> 00:37:36.882
Yeah. Already took out my usual fee.

758
00:37:41.470 --> 00:37:43.347
- Ooh. Kwan Park Technologies.
- Mmm.

759
00:37:43.430 --> 00:37:44.765
Your father-in-law. Very clever.

760
00:37:44.848 --> 00:37:46.308
[chuckles] Yeah.

761
00:37:46.850 --> 00:37:48.227
Now I get to pay taxes.

762
00:37:48.310 --> 00:37:50.312
Well. legitimate income's expensive.

763
00:37:52.064 --> 00:37:55.108
I was just very fall-prone.
Vertigo and whatnot…

764
00:37:56.026 --> 00:37:58.820
It would help if I had some sense
of future cash flow.

765
00:37:58.904 --> 00:37:59.947
Yeah. about that.

766
00:38:00.030 --> 00:38:04.326
Things are gonna be a little quiet
for some time.

767
00:38:04.409 --> 00:38:06.328
Quiet? I just got everything set up.

768
00:38:08.497 --> 00:38:10.290
- What did you do?
- I got caught.

769
00:38:10.374 --> 00:38:11.625
I'm sorry. what?

770
00:38:12.835 --> 00:38:13.877
Coop. am I exposed here?

771
00:38:13.961 --> 00:38:15.337
You're fine. Jesus. Barney.

772
00:38:15.420 --> 00:38:17.631
It's a legit question. Who caught you?

773
00:38:17.714 --> 00:38:18.841
[sighs]

774
00:38:18.924 --> 00:38:20.425
Owen Ashe.

775
00:38:20.509 --> 00:38:23.053
- Why the hell would you rob Ashe?
- Why the hell wouldn't I?

776
00:38:23.136 --> 00:38:25.889
He's like some kind
of arms dealer or something.

777
00:38:25.973 --> 00:38:27.975
- Is that true?
- I don't know. That's the rumor.

778
00:38:29.184 --> 00:38:32.229
Well. now he wants me
to manage an investment for him.

779
00:38:34.106 --> 00:38:36.817
So. he caught you robbing his house
and now he wants to hire you?

780
00:38:36.900 --> 00:38:37.943
What am I missing here?

781
00:38:38.026 --> 00:38:39.444
He's on the OFAC list.

782
00:38:41.488 --> 00:38:43.115
- Shit.
- Yeah.

783
00:38:43.615 --> 00:38:45.242
It's a sizable investment.

784
00:38:46.743 --> 00:38:47.911
How sizable?

785
00:38:49.079 --> 00:38:50.455
Extra large.

786
00:38:54.251 --> 00:38:55.502
Controversial thought.

787
00:38:56.420 --> 00:38:59.047
Maybe this is your ticket
back to the big game.

788
00:39:00.090 --> 00:39:01.675
You are taking this surprisingly well.

789
00:39:01.758 --> 00:39:02.759
I know. right?

790
00:39:03.635 --> 00:39:05.304
Crime suits me. Who knew?

791
00:39:08.473 --> 00:39:09.558
One more.

792
00:39:09.641 --> 00:39:11.351
[both moaning]

793
00:39:16.690 --> 00:39:20.110
- So. don't take this the wrong way but…
- [panting]

794
00:39:20.194 --> 00:39:21.195
[chuckles]

795
00:39:22.237 --> 00:39:24.656
That was better than usual.

796
00:39:24.740 --> 00:39:25.991
- Hmm.
- [chuckles]

797
00:39:27.409 --> 00:39:28.410
Good.

798
00:39:30.662 --> 00:39:31.663
[kisses]

799
00:39:32.206 --> 00:39:34.499
- [sighs]
- What's gotten into you?

800
00:39:35.417 --> 00:39:36.418
What? Can't a…

801
00:39:37.044 --> 00:39:39.755
Can't a man put a little energy
into pleasing his wife?

802
00:39:39.838 --> 00:39:42.007
Mmm. He sure can.

803
00:39:49.515 --> 00:39:50.682
Mmm.

804
00:39:51.767 --> 00:39:53.352
- Also…
- Hmm?

805
00:39:54.895 --> 00:39:56.647
I'm not gonna work for your father.

806
00:40:04.363 --> 00:40:05.656
I'll get you a towel.

807
00:40:07.407 --> 00:40:09.034
- …any more?
- Not a chance.

808
00:40:09.117 --> 00:40:12.496
I could see he was scared stiff
'cause he talked as much as he did.

809
00:40:12.579 --> 00:40:13.997
- [on TV] I don't get it. Johnny.
- Hey.

810
00:40:14.081 --> 00:40:15.624
About these two other guys…

811
00:40:15.707 --> 00:40:18.043
- I'm looking up Kubrick's filmography.
- [scoffs]

812
00:40:18.836 --> 00:40:20.587
Can you do it after the movie is over?

813
00:40:20.671 --> 00:40:22.965
No. I wanna be able
to contextualize as I go.

814
00:40:23.048 --> 00:40:25.133
- This is one of his first features.
- Yes. I know.

815
00:40:25.801 --> 00:40:26.927
It's impressive.

816
00:40:28.512 --> 00:40:29.680
It's fine. I guess.

817
00:40:31.640 --> 00:40:32.933
It's fine. you guess?

818
00:40:33.016 --> 00:40:35.394
- Dad.
- It's The Killing. It's a masterpiece.

819
00:40:35.477 --> 00:40:38.272
Which I'll never get to see
if you don't press play.

820
00:40:40.399 --> 00:40:42.985
I take it you'd rather not.
uh. talk about…

821
00:40:44.987 --> 00:40:47.322
- About Mom-gate?
- Is that what we're calling it?

822
00:40:47.406 --> 00:40:50.409
[inhales sharply. exhales] Dad.

823
00:40:50.492 --> 00:40:52.119
It's just… I don't know.

824
00:40:52.202 --> 00:40:53.453
It's just not very evocative.

825
00:40:53.537 --> 00:40:55.372
Sorry. I haven't focus grouped it yet.

826
00:40:56.790 --> 00:40:58.417
Can we just watch the movie?

827
00:41:01.587 --> 00:41:02.880
Fine.

828
00:41:03.881 --> 00:41:06.508
You mean there's gonna be
two other guys in on the deal

829
00:41:06.592 --> 00:41:08.135
and we ain't gonna know who they are?

830
00:41:08.218 --> 00:41:10.053
That's right. You know who they are and…

831
00:41:10.137 --> 00:41:11.638
[piano playing]

832
00:41:15.642 --> 00:41:16.894
This setup is insane.

833
00:41:17.603 --> 00:41:21.273
Yeah. My dad likes to flex
even when no one's looking.

834
00:41:21.356 --> 00:41:22.608
[knocks on door]

835
00:41:22.691 --> 00:41:25.861
Hey. Hunter. Good to see you. bud.

836
00:41:25.944 --> 00:41:26.945
Hey.

837
00:41:28.739 --> 00:41:30.616
Did you need something or…

838
00:41:30.699 --> 00:41:32.618
[Ashe] Huh? No. no. no.
No. I just heard the music.

839
00:41:32.701 --> 00:41:34.578
It sounded nice. Wanted to see
where it was coming from.

840
00:41:34.661 --> 00:41:36.663
- You play really well.
- Thanks.

841
00:41:36.747 --> 00:41:39.791
You know. I play a pretty mean guitar
if you ever feel like jamming.

842
00:41:41.418 --> 00:41:42.419
Oh. shit.

843
00:41:43.170 --> 00:41:44.421
Gotta tune these.

844
00:41:44.505 --> 00:41:45.756
[guitar playing]

845
00:41:45.839 --> 00:41:46.965
[Ashe] Ah.

846
00:41:49.009 --> 00:41:51.845
I'm gonna bounce and leave you guys to it.

847
00:41:52.471 --> 00:41:53.639
Good to see you. pal.

848
00:41:58.393 --> 00:41:59.728
Sorry about that.

849
00:42:00.521 --> 00:42:01.730
Was he any good?

850
00:42:01.813 --> 00:42:03.857
I don't know. I've never seen him play.

851
00:42:04.650 --> 00:42:06.902
I feel bad for all these guitars
wasting away.

852
00:42:06.985 --> 00:42:09.780
You should see his fencing gear
that he's used maybe. like. twice.

853
00:42:09.863 --> 00:42:13.283
ADHD and an unlimited budget
is a bad combination.

854
00:42:13.367 --> 00:42:14.368
[chuckles]

855
00:42:14.451 --> 00:42:16.161
Well. my dad plays golf

856
00:42:16.245 --> 00:42:18.830
and watches old movies
till he falls asleep so…

857
00:42:18.914 --> 00:42:20.123
That sounds awesome.

858
00:42:20.207 --> 00:42:21.208
[both chuckle]

859
00:42:24.127 --> 00:42:26.338
[chuckles] You always
make me look so much--

860
00:42:26.421 --> 00:42:28.549
Cooler. Hotter.

861
00:42:29.675 --> 00:42:30.968
[phone buzzes]

862
00:42:39.685 --> 00:42:41.979
You need to do something
about that girlfriend.

863
00:42:47.484 --> 00:42:49.319
[banging on door]

864
00:42:49.403 --> 00:42:52.239
- [person] Westmont PD.
- [banging on door]

865
00:42:53.115 --> 00:42:54.408
Stay here.

866
00:43:07.421 --> 00:43:09.631
- Hands up! Hands up!
- Whoa. whoa. whoa!

867
00:43:10.215 --> 00:43:11.633
[grunting]

868
00:43:12.467 --> 00:43:13.844
- Dad!
- [FBI agent] Andrew Cooper.

869
00:43:13.927 --> 00:43:17.264
You are under arrest for
breaking and entering and grand larceny.

870
00:43:17.347 --> 00:43:18.432
[grunts]

871
00:43:19.600 --> 00:43:21.268
It's not yours if you can't keep it.

872
00:43:21.351 --> 00:43:23.020
[police radio chatter]

873
00:43:25.480 --> 00:43:26.523
[gasps]

874
00:43:43.290 --> 00:43:45.042
[inhales deeply]

875
00:43:48.545 --> 00:43:49.546
Fuck.

876
00:43:51.507 --> 00:43:52.549
[tires screech]

877
00:44:00.974 --> 00:44:01.975
[Coop] Hey.

878
00:44:02.643 --> 00:44:03.644
Hey.

879
00:44:04.353 --> 00:44:05.354
Warm-up shot.

880
00:44:05.437 --> 00:44:06.730
[both laugh]

881
00:44:07.689 --> 00:44:08.815
So…

882
00:44:09.650 --> 00:44:10.651
did you come to play?

883
00:44:10.734 --> 00:44:12.444
Yeah. Something like that.

884
00:44:13.028 --> 00:44:14.947
All right. Lay it on me.

885
00:44:17.616 --> 00:44:18.951
Well… [sighs]

886
00:44:19.034 --> 00:44:22.246
We're gonna need to set up
four different shell companies.

887
00:44:22.329 --> 00:44:23.705
Two overseas. two here.

888
00:44:23.789 --> 00:44:26.250
And a handful of intermediary accounts.

889
00:44:26.333 --> 00:44:28.293
Great. My guys
can take care of all of that.

890
00:44:28.377 --> 00:44:29.962
Well. I'll need to oversee it.

891
00:44:31.463 --> 00:44:33.215
The Treasury Department
doesn't have the resources

892
00:44:33.298 --> 00:44:34.591
to scrutinize every transaction.

893
00:44:34.675 --> 00:44:38.095
[stammers] A billion dollars
is not exactly gonna fly under the radar.

894
00:44:38.762 --> 00:44:40.138
The number was 400 million.

895
00:44:40.222 --> 00:44:41.723
[chuckles] Where did you get a billion?

896
00:44:41.807 --> 00:44:44.810
Oh. a billion-one. actually. uh…

897
00:44:44.893 --> 00:44:46.353
The amount of money I invest

898
00:44:46.436 --> 00:44:49.106
has to be less than 40%
of money under my management

899
00:44:49.189 --> 00:44:51.441
to avoid triggering
a KYC check at Bailey's.

900
00:44:52.192 --> 00:44:54.278
- KYC?
- "Know Your Customer."

901
00:44:56.196 --> 00:44:58.949
See. this is why I need you.
'cause you know all this shit.

902
00:44:59.533 --> 00:45:02.035
So you kick back the 600
once we get into Excelsior. right?

903
00:45:02.119 --> 00:45:04.037
- If we get into Excelsior.
- Yeah.

904
00:45:04.121 --> 00:45:05.414
We're getting in.

905
00:45:05.497 --> 00:45:06.665
[chuckles]

906
00:45:06.748 --> 00:45:09.084
You know I take a 4% management fee.

907
00:45:09.168 --> 00:45:10.502
[chuckles]

908
00:45:10.586 --> 00:45:13.213
Your fee is me not having you arrested.

909
00:45:13.797 --> 00:45:15.507
- Remember?
- [chuckles]

910
00:45:15.591 --> 00:45:17.176
Come on. Let's get loaded.

911
00:45:17.259 --> 00:45:18.677
Toast our new partnership.

912
00:45:18.760 --> 00:45:20.554
- [chuckles]
- It's not a partnership.

913
00:45:20.637 --> 00:45:22.139
You're blackmailing me.

914
00:45:22.222 --> 00:45:24.224
Two things can be true at the same time.

915
00:45:28.103 --> 00:45:29.104
[sighs]

916
00:45:30.606 --> 00:45:33.025
[whistling]

917
00:45:36.820 --> 00:45:38.238
[dog barks]

918
00:45:38.947 --> 00:45:41.074
Hey! Hey! Hey!

919
00:45:41.742 --> 00:45:43.452
- Get outta here!
- [dog groans]

920
00:45:43.535 --> 00:45:44.745
Shoo! Go on.

921
00:45:52.377 --> 00:45:54.421
[breathing heavily]

922
00:46:01.261 --> 00:46:02.262
[grunts]

923
00:46:07.518 --> 00:46:08.727
- Hi.
- Hi.

924
00:46:08.810 --> 00:46:11.021
You just… You left this over at my place.

925
00:46:11.104 --> 00:46:12.272
Oh.

926
00:46:15.901 --> 00:46:17.277
What the…

927
00:46:17.361 --> 00:46:18.904
What the fuck is this?

928
00:46:18.987 --> 00:46:20.197
[Mel] You're welcome.

929
00:46:21.281 --> 00:46:22.282
[groans]

930
00:46:23.700 --> 00:46:24.743
[sniffs]

931
00:46:41.969 --> 00:46:43.095
[phone buzzing]

932
00:46:47.641 --> 00:46:50.269
- Hey. what's up?
- I have our next house.

933
00:46:53.272 --> 00:46:55.774
Yeah. I-I… [sighs]
Man. I don't think I can do it.

934
00:46:55.858 --> 00:46:57.734
My-My back's been seizing up all week.

935
00:46:57.818 --> 00:46:59.194
[sighs] Come on. Coop.

936
00:46:59.278 --> 00:47:00.654
I have a good window.

937
00:47:00.737 --> 00:47:03.657
They're away for a week.
Easy in. easy out. Just like Ashe.

938
00:47:03.740 --> 00:47:07.536
Well. I was feeling better then.
and now the pain's been pretty intense.

939
00:47:07.619 --> 00:47:10.497
- So I don't think I can do it.
- It's a good window. Coop.

940
00:47:10.581 --> 00:47:11.832
I'm sure it is.

941
00:47:13.166 --> 00:47:14.293
Okay.

942
00:47:15.794 --> 00:47:18.964
Well. then how about
you drive and I go in?

943
00:47:19.548 --> 00:47:20.966
That's not how we do it.

944
00:47:21.049 --> 00:47:24.678
Well. maybe we should change how we do it
if your back is gonna be a problem.

945
00:47:24.761 --> 00:47:26.847
It's… it's not a problem.

946
00:47:26.930 --> 00:47:28.056
I just need a little time.

947
00:47:31.476 --> 00:47:32.477
Okay.

948
00:47:33.312 --> 00:47:35.314
- Feel better. viejo.
- Thank you.

949
00:47:37.858 --> 00:47:39.902
Jesus. Sneaking up.

950
00:47:39.985 --> 00:47:41.236
Sorry.

951
00:47:41.320 --> 00:47:42.321
Make some noise. you know.

952
00:47:42.404 --> 00:47:44.489
or I'm gonna have to hang
a bell around your neck.

953
00:47:45.407 --> 00:47:46.408
[groans]

954
00:47:47.576 --> 00:47:48.660
Is your back bothering you?

955
00:47:48.744 --> 00:47:49.745
Yeah.

956
00:47:53.373 --> 00:47:55.250
Never get old. my friend.

957
00:47:57.127 --> 00:47:58.837
[groans] Something on your mind?

958
00:47:58.921 --> 00:48:00.005
Yeah.

959
00:48:01.673 --> 00:48:05.093
I'm wondering how to write a breakup text.

960
00:48:05.177 --> 00:48:07.221
[exhales sharply] That's easy. You don't.

961
00:48:08.222 --> 00:48:10.140
Breaking up
should always be done in person.

962
00:48:10.224 --> 00:48:12.142
- Always?
- Yes.

963
00:48:12.226 --> 00:48:13.727
Whether you're dating
or you're breaking up.

964
00:48:13.810 --> 00:48:15.270
the rules are the same.

965
00:48:15.979 --> 00:48:17.564
- What rules?
- Don't be a dick.

966
00:48:18.565 --> 00:48:20.943
It'd be so much easier
just to write a text.

967
00:48:21.026 --> 00:48:22.861
[chuckles] Yeah. I'm sure it would.

968
00:48:24.112 --> 00:48:25.239
[sighs]

969
00:48:25.989 --> 00:48:27.199
Something happen?

970
00:48:27.282 --> 00:48:28.951
Uh. yeah.

971
00:48:29.910 --> 00:48:31.161
What's her name?

972
00:48:32.412 --> 00:48:33.455
Delilah.

973
00:48:36.166 --> 00:48:38.043
Ashe's daughter. huh?

974
00:48:38.126 --> 00:48:39.127
Yeah.

975
00:48:40.587 --> 00:48:42.047
Yeah. she's pretty cool.

976
00:48:44.216 --> 00:48:47.386
Well. you gotta deal with Morgan first.

977
00:48:47.469 --> 00:48:48.762
In person.

978
00:48:49.346 --> 00:48:50.639
Okay.

979
00:48:50.722 --> 00:48:52.224
Then see what's up.

980
00:48:53.934 --> 00:48:55.143
All right. well. good talk.

981
00:48:56.186 --> 00:48:57.187
You want a beer?

982
00:48:58.480 --> 00:48:59.481
- Yeah.
- No.

983
00:48:59.565 --> 00:49:01.108
[chuckles] Nice try.

984
00:49:01.191 --> 00:49:02.693
But you can get me one.

985
00:49:02.776 --> 00:49:04.278
Okay. [scoffs]

986
00:49:05.529 --> 00:49:06.655
Thank you.

987
00:49:08.615 --> 00:49:09.992
[sighs]

988
00:49:45.027 --> 00:49:46.028
[engine revs]

989
00:49:51.617 --> 00:49:53.911
- [engine revs]
- [tires screech]

990
00:49:55.621 --> 00:49:57.456
[chattering]

991
00:49:58.957 --> 00:50:01.376
We're looking for
a different fee structure. okay?

992
00:50:02.002 --> 00:50:04.838
Listen. I sat on your side of the table
long enough to know when it's bullshit.

993
00:50:11.303 --> 00:50:14.640
[Coop] Nothing beats the thrill of hitting
the street with a big chunk of change.

994
00:50:16.433 --> 00:50:18.852
Even when the change
in question isn't yours…

995
00:50:18.936 --> 00:50:19.937
Hey. Coop. How are you?

996
00:50:20.020 --> 00:50:22.147
…and you're hitting the street
under duress.

997
00:50:23.315 --> 00:50:25.108
I was the toast of the town.

998
00:50:27.110 --> 00:50:28.737
Everyone singing for their supper

999
00:50:28.820 --> 00:50:30.072
while they paid for mine.

1000
00:50:31.490 --> 00:50:33.700
[adviser] Don't waste your time
chasing Medallion.

1001
00:50:33.784 --> 00:50:35.827
Roanoke outpaced them two years straight.

1002
00:50:36.495 --> 00:50:38.330
And here I thought Roanoke
was a closed fund.

1003
00:50:38.872 --> 00:50:40.207
For some people.

1004
00:50:40.290 --> 00:50:43.544
[Coop] It was surreal. really.
how fast I could slip back into it.

1005
00:50:44.545 --> 00:50:46.797
The patter.
the ball-busting. the bullshit.

1006
00:50:48.549 --> 00:50:51.552
And I'd be lying if I said there wasn't
a part of me that had missed it.

1007
00:50:51.635 --> 00:50:54.763
Because this… I knew how to do this.

1008
00:50:55.389 --> 00:50:56.390
[Josh] Bullshit.

1009
00:50:56.473 --> 00:51:00.018
We can… We wanna be
in the Andrew Cooper business long-term.

1010
00:51:00.102 --> 00:51:01.395
But what about the fee structure?

1011
00:51:01.478 --> 00:51:03.814
We can talk about a cap
for the first two years.

1012
00:51:03.897 --> 00:51:06.149
Well. it was great catching up. Coop.

1013
00:51:06.233 --> 00:51:07.693
I knew you'd be back.

1014
00:51:07.776 --> 00:51:09.236
It was just a question of when.

1015
00:51:09.319 --> 00:51:10.404
I don't believe you.

1016
00:51:10.487 --> 00:51:12.114
[Coop] The game hadn't changed.

1017
00:51:12.197 --> 00:51:13.198
It never does.

1018
00:51:13.991 --> 00:51:17.160
And I had to remind myself
that I was here to play a different one.

1019
00:51:18.120 --> 00:51:20.247
And that game was just getting started.
